text: Kulushevo () is a rural locality (a village) in Urazovsky Selsoviet, Uchalinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 151 as of 2010. There are 6 streets. == Geography == It is located 48 km from Uchaly, 24 km from Urazovo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Uchalinsky District
title: Kulushevo, Uchalinsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan
